cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.DS, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a deep learning method for detecting specific types of reads in the de novo genome assembly process. The method uses coverage graphs converted to 1D-signals and employs a semi-supervised approach to reduce the need for labeled data. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the following arXiv CS sub-categories: 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning)
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence)
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition)
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms)
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing)
